```
file: crates/ctx-cage/src/lifecycle/prepare.rs
behavior: Lifecycle phase 1 of a cage run: gates billed modes on a clean git tree, mints a per-run tempdir, materializes the rules file and a secret-mask file, and resolves the claude runtime when billed.
edit_notes:
  - Billed-mode detection via mode_is_billed(&r.mode) gates both the clean-tree check and claude runtime resolution; keep these two gated together since the read-write cage mount only makes "recovery is plain git" valid when starting from a clean commit.
  - Mask file must be a real empty regular file, not /dev/null, because bind mounts carry nodev.
  - Rundir path is deterministic (ctxcage-<task_id>-<pid>) and any pre-existing dir at that path is silently removed before recreation.
functions:
  - name: prepare_run
    signature: pub fn prepare_run(r: &Resolved) -> Result<Prep, CageError>
    purpose: Runs the full phase-1 setup sequence and returns the Prep bundle consumed by later lifecycle phases.
    notes: Returns CageError::Protocol for dirty tree or missing claude runtime/credential; CageError::Io for filesystem failures.
invariants:
  - claude field is Some iff mode_is_billed(&r.mode) is true.
  - ensure_clean_tree errors unless target_root is a git repo with a clean porcelain status or allow_dirty is set.
external_deps:
  - git (external binary via Command): sole mechanism for the dirty-tree check; failure to invoke or non-git-repo output is treated as CageError::Protocol.
```